An absolute let down. The first red flag should have been that we had to track down our waiter to order our drinks. The second red flag should have been the drinks were inedible. Truly truly terrible. The third red flag should have been trying to track down our waiter again to pay on what was not a busy night. The fourth red flag should have been that despite having only seen our waiter once when we ordered drinks, he said we needed to order food as we asked for the check. Concerned about spending any more money (as the prices at this place are sky high) on anything additionally inedible, he brought the manager to our table. She informed us the waiter had told her he had asked us multiple times to order food, despite having only come to our table once. She proceeded to accuse us of lying. To add insult to injury, as she took our check (which included a 20 percent hidden required service fee—though for what service I am not certain) she dropped our credit card and then refused to pick it up. I was shocked at how hostile she got. Horrible service, horrendous drinks, though certainly a very well decorated restaurant. Avoid it if you want a nice night.   Clearly, I should have read the other reviews before coming.....

The empanadas are really flavorful, the chicken & beef tacos are extremely delicious, the crispy brussels are amazing. And those are the appetizers. Went for brunch after church. Very underwhelming service. We were initially seated inside but decided to move to the patio because it was such a nice day. Had to wait 5 minutes before we were brought water and had to flag down a server to order the bottomless brunch and place our order. Our actual server brought out the drinks in a carafe-type container and we essentially never saw her again.  The food was good - breakfast burritos and chicken and waffles - the home fries were also excellent. Because it was such a nice day our bottomless drinks in the carafe warmed quickly and our server was no where to be found. She stopped by once to ask how our food was before we had even taken a bite and had to be flagged down to get the check.  I’m usually a generous tipper regardless of how good the service is but after the meal I only tipped around 5-6% as a result of the lack of service.  The food wasn’t bad and if DC didn’t have so many other good options I would likely give it a chance.

Lost my phone there last night. Was told I could not go in to look for it because I was "too intoxicated." I was just explaining that my phone was inside and that my friend who I share my location with places my phone there. Maybe I was distraught? Seems perfectly normal to me when you look in your purse and don't see your phone? This was right after the other bouncer at the door was helping me by calling my phone on his personal phone which I thought was very kind. I was having a perfectly normal conversation with him, but for some reason, the other bouncer did not let me inside. I had been drinking but I was no way near "too intoxicated." Even IF I was too intoxicated.... you're just going to make me walk away BY MYSELF with NO phone? I left my friends at the other bar to go and GET my phone, but when I COULDN'T get it, I had no way to get back in contact with my friends. So I taxi home (40 minute ride), call them (P.14), and what do you know, THEY HAVE MY PHONE. Wow wasn't I just there telling them they had my phone????? At this point it is 2am. When I called, they said they had it and they close at 3. I confirmed this. 3? Ok I'm coming. I get a ride there (another 40 minutes back to where I JUST was) and show up at 2:45 for all the doors to be locked. I tried banging on the doors and saw people see me but nobody came down.  If some guy had not gone out the side door to take a smoke, I would not have my phone. Completely appalled that I was telling the bouncers from the beginning that my phone was INSIDE and rather than offering to check or anything, or even letting me in to go look myself, they turned me away. Alone. Without my phone. and "too intoxicated."

As for brunch we had the Maryland crab benedict, brunch burrito and steak benedict. The benedict's had the perfect egg. The crab was lump and cooked perfectly. Don't skip the steak if you love some quality steak. Right around 2 PM on Sunday the upstairs opened up and the place got even more packed. Overall, my friends and I really enjoyed this spot. The cocktails are definitely unique and the food here is delicious. I'll definitely be back to sample some more of their cocktails

I also got the Hot Tennessee Fried Chicken burger with truffle fries (omg so good!) and I opted to have them put the sauce on the side because I was worried about how spicy it would be. The sauce ended up being spicy but delicious so I added some to the sandwich myself and ate the whole thing! It’s a good sized piece of chicken so you could take half home for leftovers if you wanted. I was so full from the burger that I couldn’t finish the fries, sadly, but was overall satisfied!

wanna feel disrespected after paying a 40 dollar cover and 8 more to check in a coat? Came here for NYE. At the end of our night, we were in a rush to leave to catch the last metro home and avoid a $200 Uber. I got to the line at 1:20 AM and gave my ticket number and showed my picture of it to the coat check person. I was still waiting 20 minutes later as he was grabbing other people's coats for them efficiently. I believe they knew the coat wasn't there but continued helping other people, letting me and my friends stand there for that long and causing us to miss the Metro home.  Had to talk to 2 different managers, the 2nd offered to pay for our Uber home. When he was finally going to call 20 minutes later, he refused when he realized we needed an Uber XL for the 6 people he made wait (which he didn't initially realize because he rudely told my friends to go stand inside instead of clogging the stairwell, so he thought there was only 2 people). he ran upstairs in a tantrum and didn't come back. we had to wait until he finally came and gave us $100 at 2:30 AM. Overall felt disrespected by management and a lack of caring on their part. I should be able to trust them to handle my jacket if I pay them $8 dollars, and to swiftly take responsibility instead of saying "sorry, this could be your fault or ours, we're not sure.." but instead, the coat check person was extremely incompetent and the management tried to be caring but ended up stomping out when they couldn't handle customers' rightful complaints, and they couldn't take responsibility when it was 100% their fault for being unable to their only job - matching a number to a coat. I appreciated them taking my info and attempting to call me, though. thanks for that, but still a horrible way to end our night.

I went to Provision last night to grab dinner, they said it would be a 30 min wait. So, my friend and I left to go to another bar for a drink. I went to check Provision’s website to see if there were reservation times open...and there were plenty open. I thought that was strange, but I went ahead and booked my reservation to guarantee a table at 10:45pm. When we arrived, we told the bouncer we had a reservation and he was completely rude. He said it didn’t matter if we had a reservation, he said get in the line (mind you this is a restaurant/bar, not a club). He got an attitude when I showed him the reservation, and begrudgingly went in to ask the hostess to talk to us. The hostess came out and said the kitchen closes at 11pm, so they couldn’t serve us. I was confused by this because you shouldn’t have an online reservation system (Open table) have reservation times that your restaurant WON’T honor. I’d say if you want to get late dinner maybe try another place or go earlier in the day so you don’t have to deal with lines outside and a discourteous bouncer.

Went here for brunch and had the fried chicken and biscuits. When we initially sat down it did take a while for someone to come greet us and take our drink orders. Not sure if they thought we had more people coming because they sat us at a larger table. Eventually, after about 15 minutes someone came and got our order. Food was absolutely delicious. The portion sizes are huge and the chicken it self was very well seasoned. The biscuit was a little dry, but they gave us butter and honey so it made it better. We also had the coffee and the bottomless mimosas. The coffee was just your basic coffee. The mimosas were delicious! I wasn't a huge fan of the basil mimosas, but the regular ones were great. Service was a little slow, and there wasn't someone checking on us regularly so we did have to flag someone down occasionally. However, we never ran out of mimosas and they did make sure our glasses were full! Overall, I would definitely go back.

The ambience is lovely, very chill and warm. The later it gets, it turns into a lounge with dope music. I love this place. The food was good too and the drinks are ace. Highly recommend if you're looking for a hip bar/lounge/dinner hybrid vibe.
